Example
Get the color resolution of your screen:

Copy
let x = "Color Resolution: " + screen.pixelDepth;

Description
The pixelDepth property returns the color resolution in bits per pixel of the visitor's screen.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
pixelDepth	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
let a = screen.pixelDepth;
Return Value
A Number, representing the color resolution, in bits per pixel.

Possible values:

1 bit per pixel
4 bits per pixel
8 bits per pixel
15 bits per pixel
16 bits per pixel
24 bits per pixel
32 bits per pixel
48 bits per pixel
